  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Dental Receptionist",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Location: Hougang </strong></h3><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Register patients and manage appointment scheduling efficiently</p></li><li><p>Attend to phone calls, WhatsApp messages, and walk-in enquiries professionally</p></li><li><p>Handle patient enquiries regarding treatments, fees, and clinic policies</p></li><li><p>Provide basic financial counselling and assist with payment-related queries</p></li><li><p>Perform accurate data entry, filing, and maintenance of patient records</p></li><li><p>Support day-to-day clinic operations, including maintaining a clean and organised reception area</p></li><li><p>Assist with general administrative and ad-hoc duties as required</p></li><li><p>Work rotating shifts, including nights and/or weekends, based on clinic roster</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Basic computer literacy (comfortable with appointment systems, WhatsApp, and email)</p></li><li><p>Good communication and interpersonal skills</p></li><li><p>Pleasant, patient-oriented, and service-driven attitude</p></li><li><p>Able to multitask and remain calm in a fast-paced clinical environment</p></li><li><p>Prior experience in a dental or healthcare clinic is an advantage</p></li><li><p>Training will be provided for candidates without prior dental experience</p></li></ul><h3><strong>What We Offer</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Structured on-the-job training</p></li><li><p>Supportive team environment</p></li><li><p>Exposure to a professional dental practice setting</p></li><li><p>Opportunities for growth and skills development</p></li></ul><p><strong>Interested candidates may apply with their resume or contact us directly for more information.</strong></p>",
